Qualifications: KDF1 was tandem affinity purified from differentiated keratinocytes labeled in a SILAC (stable isotope labeling by amino acids in cell culture) experiment in which cells containing tagged target were labeled with heavy isotope and control (untagged) cells were labeled with light isotope and associated proteins were identified by mass spectrometry in two separate experiments; a protein was considered a valid interactor in either experiment if it had a log2 normalized high-to-low ratio of greater than 1 or if only heavy-labeled protein was identified; a protein was considered an interactor if the interaction was valid in one experiment and either valid or not observed in the other experiment.
